.TH "dev_get_stats" 9 "dev_get_stats" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dev_get_stats \- get network device statistics
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct rtnl_link_stats64 *" dev_get_stats
.BI "(struct net_device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct rtnl_link_stats64 *storage "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
device to get statistics from
.IP "storage" 12
place to store stats

Get network statistics from device. Return \fIstorage\fP.
The device driver may provide its own method by setting
dev->netdev_ops->get_stats64 or dev->netdev_ops->get_stats;
otherwise the internal statistics structure is used.
